b. At least five (5) years' post graduate programming experience on IBM mainframe z/OS and CICS operating environment using TSO, ISPF, COBOL for z/OS, CICS COBOL, JCL and other utilities;
c. At least five (5) years' post graduate hands-on programming experience using COBOL for z/OS and CICS COBOL in processing IBM VSAM and sequential files and able to maintain VSAM file structure;
d. At least five (5) years' post graduate working experience in preparing JCL for compilation, linkage and execution of COBOL for z/OS programs, Sort and other IBM Utilities;
e. At least five (5) years' post graduate hands-on programming experience using DB2/SQL in COBOL for z/OS and CICS COBOL programs;
f. Able to use ISPF Editor to write and maintain programs and JCLs;
g. Able to code BMS Macro and the various field macro parameters to define all the map elements and their characteristics and to assemble the coded source into physical and symbolic map layout for the application program;
h. Able to handle job compilation using JES2 and analyse compilation result using SDSF facilities;
i. Able to debug JCLs and programs written in COBOL for z/OS and CICS COBOL;
j. Able to use ISPF and JCLs and programs to prepare test data and test data sets;
k. Able to conduct unit, module, functional and volume tests; to analyse the test results and to take corrective actions.
